Simple string literal should be used for single line strings
Why is this an issue? If a string fits on a single line, without concatenation and escaped newlines, you should probably continue to use a string literal. 
### Noncompliant
String question = """
              What's the point, really?""";
 
### Compliant
String question = "What's the point, really?";
